38 //
39 // Base class for all environment models, providing separate collision check
40 // functions for each type of tracking error bound. All environments are
41 // boxes in 3D space. Environment is templated on the specific type of sensor
42 // message (M) which may be generated from or incpororated into a derived class,
43 // and a sensor service (S) which may be used to generate sensor readings.
44 //
46

48 #define FASTRACK_ENVIRONMENT_ENVIRONMENT_H

61 template<typename M, typename S>
62 class Environment {
63 public:
64  virtual ~Environment() {}
65 
66  // Initialize from a ROS NodeHandle.
67  bool Initialize(const ros::NodeHandle& n);
68 
69  // Derived classes must provide a collision checker which returns true if
70  // and only if the provided position is a valid collision-free configuration.
71  // Provide a separate collision check for each type of tracking error bound.
72  virtual bool IsValid(const Vector3d& position, const Box& bound) const = 0;
73 
74  // Utility for checking multiple positions.
75  bool AreValid(const std::vector<Vector3d>& positions, const Box& bound) const;
76 
77  // Derived classes must have some sort of visualization through RViz.
78  virtual void Visualize() const = 0;
79 
80 protected:
81  explicit Environment()
82  : initialized_(false) {}
83 
84  // Load parameters. This may be overridden by derived classes if needed
85  // (they should still call this one via Environment::LoadParameters).
86  virtual bool LoadParameters(const ros::NodeHandle& n);
87 
88  // Register callbacks.
89  bool RegisterCallbacks(const ros::NodeHandle& n);
90 
91  // Update this environment with the information contained in the given
92  // sensor measurement.
93  virtual void SensorCallback(const M::ConstPtr& msg) = 0;
94 
95  // Generate a sensor measurement as a service response.
96  virtual bool SensorServer(
97  typename S::Request& req, typename S::Response& res) = 0;
98 
99  // Upper and lower bounds.
100  Vector3d lower_;
101  Vector3d upper_;
102 
103  // Publisher and subscriber.
104  ros::Publisher vis_pub_;
105  ros::Subscriber sensor_sub_;
106 
107  std::string vis_topic_;
108  std::string sensor_topic_;
109 
110  // Service.
111  ros::ServiceServer sensor_srv_;
112  std::string sensor_srv_name_;
113 
114  // Frame in which to publish visualization.
115  std::string fixed_frame_;
116 
117  // Naming and initialization.
118  std::string name_;
119  bool initialized_;
120 }; //\class Environment

124 // Initialize from a ROS NodeHandle.
125 template<typename M, typename S>
126 bool Environment<M, S>::Initialize(const ros::NodeHandle& n) {
127  name_ = ros::names::append(n.getNamespace(), "Environment");
128 
129  if (!LoadParameters(n)) {
130  ROS_ERROR("%s: Failed to load parameters.", name_.c_str());
131  return false;
132  }
133 
134  if (!RegisterCallbacks(n)) {
135  ROS_ERROR("%s: Failed to register callbacks.", name_.c_str());
136  return false;
137  }
138 
139  initialized_ = true;
140  return true;
141 }
142 
143 // Load parameters. This may be overridden by derived classes if needed
144 // (they should still call this one via Environment::LoadParameters).
145 template<typename M, typename S>
146 bool Environment<M, S>::LoadParameters(const ros::NodeHandle& n) {
147  ros::NodeHandle nl(n);
148 
149  // Sensor topic/service.
150  if (!nl.getParam("topic/sensor", sensor_topic_)) return false;
151  if (!nl.getParam("srv/sensor", sensor_srv_name_)) return false;
152 
153  // Frame of reference to publish visualization in.
154  if (!nl.getParam("frame/fixed", fixed_frame_)) return false;
155 
156  // Upper and lower bounds of the environment.
157  if (!nl.getParam("env/upper/x", upper_(0))) return false;
158  if (!nl.getParam("env/upper/y", upper_(1))) return false;
159  if (!nl.getParam("env/upper/z", upper_(2))) return false;
160 
161  if (!nl.getParam("env/lower/x", lower_(0))) return false;
162  if (!nl.getParam("env/lower/y", lower_(1))) return false;
163  if (!nl.getParam("env/lower/z", lower_(2))) return false;
164 
165  return true;
166 }
167 
168 // Register callbacks.
169 template<typename M, typename S>
170 bool Environment<M, S>::RegisterCallbacks(const ros::NodeHandle& n) {
171  ros::NodeHandle nl(n);
172 
173  // Subscribers.
174  sensor_sub_ = nl.subscribe(
175  sensor_topic_.c_str(), 1, &Environment<M, S>::SensorCallback, this);
176 
177  // Publishers.
178  vis_pub_ = nl.advertise<visualization_msgs::Marker>(
179  vis_topic_.c_str(), 1, false);
180 
181  // Services.
182  sensor_srv_ = nl.advertiseService(sensor_srv_name_.c_str(),
183  &Environment<M, S>::SensorServer, this);
184 
185  return true;
186 }
187 
188 // Provide auxiliary validity checkers for sets of positions.
189 template<typename M, typename S>
190 bool Environment<M, S>::AreValid(
191  const std::vector<Vector3d>& positions, const Box& bound) const {
192  // Return Boolean AND of all IsValid calls.
193  for (const auto& p : positions) {
194  if (!IsValid(p, bound))
195  return false;
196  }
197 
198  return true;
199 }
